1.name: Clift Hotel
1.description: A 6-minute walk from Union Square and 4 minutes from a Muni Metro station, this luxury hotel designed by Philippe Starck features an artsy furniture collection in the lobby, including work by Salvador Dali.

2.name: W San Francisco
2.description: Less than a block from the Yerba Buena Center for the Arts, this trendy hotel is a 12-minute walk from Union Square.

3.name: Hotel Zetta
3.description: A 3-minute walk from the Powell Street cable-car turnaround and BART rail station, this hip hotel 9 minutes from Union Square combines high-tech lodging with artsy touches.

4.name: Hotel Vitale
4.description: This waterfront hotel with Bay Bridge views is 3 blocks from the Financial District and a 4-minute walk from the Ferry Building.

5.name: Phoenix Hotel
5.description: Located in the Tenderloin neighborhood, a 10-minute walk from a BART rail station, this retro motor lodge has hosted many rock musicians and other celebrities since the 1950s. It’s a 4-minute walk from the historic Great American Music Hall nightclub.

6.name: St. Regis San Francisco
6.description: St. Regis Museum Tower is a 42-story, 484 ft skyscraper in the South of Market district of San Francisco, California, adjacent to Yerba Buena Gardens, Moscone Center, PacBell Building and the San Francisco Museum of Modern Art.
